***28-9-2025 Sunday***
***Day 2. Linux Practice***

1. Check all currently running processes.
2. Find the process ID (PID) of a specific process.
3. Kill a process using its PID.
4. Display the last 10 lines of a file.
5. Monitor real-time system resource usage (CPU, memory).
7. Search for a specific word in a file.
8. Display the first 5 lines of a file.
9. Create a symbolic link for a file.
10. Change file permissions and ownership.

***Solution***

1. ps aux
2. ps aux | grep process_name
3. kill 33
4. tail filename.txt  
5. touch empty.txt
6. top
7. grep "line" filename.txt 
8. tail filename.txt
9. touch filename.txt | pwd | find /home/tanisha -name "filename.txt" | ln -s /home/tanisha/filename.txt myline.txt | cat mylink.txt
10. chmod 755 filename.txt | chown user:group filename.txt